'''Srikrishna Alanahalli''' (3 April 1947 – 4 January 1989) was an Indian [[novelist]] and [[poet]]. The majority of his works are written in the [[Kannada language]]. He became popular for his novels ''Kaadu'' (1972), ''Parasangada Gendethimma'' (1978) and ''Bhujangayyana Dasavataragalu'' (1982), all of his novels were adapted into films.<ref>{{cite web |title= A writer ahead of his time |url= http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/lounge/A-writer-ahead-of-his-time/articleshow/23988116.cms |publisher= ''Bangalore Mirror'' |date= 11 October 2013 |accessdate= 7 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= Call of the primordial |url= http://www.thehindu.com/features/magazine/call-of-the-primordial/article5308322.ece |newspaper= The Hindu |date= 3 November 2013 |accessdate= 9 May 2014}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Alanahalli was born on April 3, 1947 in Alanahalli, [[Kingdom of Mysore]] (now [[Karnataka]]).{{Citation needed|date= April 2018}} He received his Master of Arts in Philosophy in 1969 and worked as a lecturer at [[Mysore University]] and the [[Central Institute of Indian Languages]] from 1969 to 1979.{{Citation needed|date= April 2018}} He then became a full-time writer and immersed himself in different fields, such as literature, cinema, agriculture, and journalism. He also actively took part in contemporary politics.{{Citation needed|date= April 2018}}

==Literary career==

Alanahalli's ''Parasangada Gendethimma'' novel was made into a Kannada  film [[Parasangada Gendethimma|of the same name]] with [[Lokesh]] playing the lead role of Gendethimma. He won the [[Karnataka State Film Award for Best Actor]].

Alanahalli edited a bi-monthly Sameekshana and ran a publishing house of the same name. He has 12 books to his credit, including three collections of poems. He translated Dogri Pahari love poems into [[Kannada]].{{Citation needed|date= April 2018}}

==Major Works==

'''Short Stories/ಕಥಾಸಂಕಲನ''' 
* Tapta/ತಪ್ತ 
* Geejagana Goodu/ಗೀಜಗನ ಗೂಡು 
* Finix/ಫಿನಿಕ್ಸ್ 
* Samagra Kathegalu/ಸಮಗ್ರ ಕತೆಗಳು 
* Srikrishna Aalanahalli Sahitya Vachike&nbsp;— Ed: Vivek Shanbhag/ಶ್ರೀಕೃಷ್ಣ ಆಲನಹಳ್ಳಿ ಸಾಹಿತ್ಯ ವಾಚಿಕೆ - ಸಂ: ವಿವೇಕ ಶಾನಭಾಗ

'''Poetry/ಕಾವ್ಯ''' 
* Mannina Haadu/ಮಣ್ಣಿನ ಹಾಡು 
* Kaadu Gidada Haadu Paadu/ಕಾಡುಗಿಡದ ಹಾಡು ಪಾಡು 
* Dogri Pahaadi Premageetegalu/ಡೇೂಗ್ರಿ ಪಹಾಡಿ ಪ್ರೇಮಗೀತೆಗಳು

'''Novels/ಕಾದಂಬರಿಗಳು''' 
* Kaadu/ಕಾಡು
* Parasangada Gendethimma/ಪರಸಂಗದ ಗಂಡೆತಿಮ್ಮ 
* Bujangayyana Dashavataragalu/ಭುಜಂಗಯ್ಯನ ದಶಾವತಾರಗಳು 
* Gode/ಗೇೂಡೆ (Sequel to Kaadu)

'''Novels/Short Stories Made into Movies''' 
* [[Kaadu (1973 Kannada film)|Kaadu]] - Kannada Movie  (1973)
* [[Parasangada Gendethimma]] - Kannada Movie (1979)
* Geejagana Goodu — Kannada Movie (1975)
* Kurubara Lakkanoo Elizebheth Raaniyoo — Kannada Movie (1976)
* [[Bhujangayyana Dashavathara]] - Kannada Movie (1988)
*[[Kannil Theriyum Kathaikal]] (Tamil)
*[[Rosappu Ravikkaikari]] (Tamil)

==Major awards==

* [[Karnataka Sahitya Akademi Award for Poetry]] ''Mannina Haadu (1966)''
* Karnataka Government Prize for Kaadu (1970)
* Karnataka Sahitya Academy Honorary Award for Lifetime Achievement (1989)

